the units for CO2 fluxes have been challenged. The issue is under review.
10-1-2003 Sven Bohm. Unit problems resoved. CO2 units changed from g C/ha/day to kg C/ha/day
12-16-2004 Sven Bohm. A reminder note that the gas samples in 1995 were only run for CH4 due to the long storage times between sampling and analysis as well as the discovery that the rubber seals used tended to leak quite rapidly

4-11-2006 Sven Bohm. Prior to 2000 two repliate chambers were used in the forested treatments
column3: they were reported as reps 1 through 6. They map on the current sampling scheme as rep 1-2 is R1
column4: rep 3-4 is R2 and rep 5-6 is R3
